history.content: You can go to any discussion. They also post the discussion notes on the course site IIRC, though to get exam clobbering you need to attend a certain percentage of discussions [email head TA or someone just to get official confirmation that if you attend another discussion section you still get counted towards that].

No*.


"Labs for this class are not open section, you must go to your assigned lab section. If you finish the lab early, we encourage you to help other groups debug their lab. This will help you learn the material better and contribute towards a better learning experience for everyone." 

from 

http://inst.eecs.berkeley.edu/~ee16a/fa17/#policies

*I would email the TA of the lab you're currently enrolled in, and the TA of the lab you're trying to enroll in, and ask if it's possible to switch.

Can you also go to any lab section? I'm afraid of trying to swap lab sections right now lest I get dropped from the class (I'm currently enrolled), but was just wondering if it is possible to go consistently to another lab section.
